Inside Scoop

Not Just Buffett: IBM Unit Sells IBM, Wells Fargo
The IBM Retirement Fund has sold off stocks, not even sparing its own. At least it still has more Apple than IBM.


 







By

Ed Lin

 Biography




 




Updated May 12, 2017 1:09 p.m. ET


International Business Machines’ pension fund recently took a merciless axe to its equities portfolio in the last quarter, and not even its parent was spared.  IBM (ticker: IBM) Retirement Fund chopped down holdings in its company’s stock to 12,451 shares as of March 31 from 82,802 on Dec. 31. It also broke the bank with Wells Fargo (WFC), reducing its stake to 65,000 shares from over 430,000. Warren Buffett made headlines as...
	      




 


